-- Bank of Italy says bad loans up 20.5 pct in July
-- 
-- Tue Sep 09, 2014 04:41AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, Sept 9 (Reuters) - The Bank of Italy said on Tuesday bad loans in the country were up 20.5 percent year-on-year in July while lending to companies and families continued to contract.

In June, non-performing loans had risen 20.8 percent on an annual basis.